    {
      "id": "n5",
      "type": "Note",
      "params": {
        "text": "TRUE 3D VORONOI — Populate fills the sphere's VOLUME with 60 seeded points (wire a solid into region and it samples inside, not in a box). Voronoi3D turns each point into a convex mesh cell, shrunk to 0.85 and clipped to the same sphere; Mesh Subtract carves the cells out, and what remains — the walls BETWEEN cells — is the lattice. count/seed set the pattern, scale sets the wall thickness (1.0 = no walls, nothing left). Preview n3 to see the raw cells; MeshToSolid bridges back to B-Rep if you must fillet it."
      },
      "position": [60, 420]
    }
